msgctxt "mn83:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 83 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 83 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: Maghadevasutta → makhā­deva­suttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "mn83:0.2"
msgid "Maghadevasutta "
msgstr "About King Makhādeva "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn83:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn83:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā mithilāyaṃ viharati maghadevaambavane. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Mithilā in the Makhādeva Mango Grove. "

#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn83:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā aññatarasmiṃ padese sitaṃ pātvākāsi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha smiled at a certain spot. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn83:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda thought, "

msgctxt "mn83:2.3"
msgid "“ko nu kho hetu, ko paccayo bhagavato sitassa pātukammāya? "
msgstr "“What is the cause, what is the reason why the Buddha smiled? "

msgctxt "mn83:2.4"
msgid "Na akāraṇena tathāgatā sitaṃ pātukarontī”ti. "
msgstr "Realized Ones do not smile for no reason.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn83:2.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando ekaṃsaṃ cīvaraṃ katvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "So Ānanda got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said, "

msgctxt "mn83:2.6"
msgid "“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo bhagavato sitassa pātukammāya? "
msgstr "“What is the cause, what is the reason why the Buddha smiled? "

msgctxt "mn83:2.7"
msgid "Na akāraṇena tathāgatā sitaṃ pātukarontī”ti. "
msgstr "Realized Ones do not smile for no reason.” "

# NOTE: In such contexts, dhamma approaches the later Hindu use of svadharma, i.e. the duty appropriate for ones’ station. Compare the rukkhadhamma at AN 6.54
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, pts-vp-pli2.75, sc2
msgctxt "mn83:3.1"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, ānanda, imissāyeva mithilāyaṃ rājā ahosi maghadevo nāma dhammiko dhammarājā dhamme ṭhito mahārājā; "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, Ānanda, right here in Mithilā there was a just and principled king named Makhādeva, a great king who stood by his duty. "

msgctxt "mn83:3.2"
msgid "dhammaṃ carati brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca; "
msgstr "He justly treated brahmins and householders, and people of town and country. "

msgctxt "mn83:3.3"
msgid "uposathañca upavasati cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassa. "
msgstr "And he observed the sabbath on the fourteenth, fifteenth, and eighth of the fortnight. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4
msgctxt "mn83:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, rājā maghadevo bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena kappakaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then, after many years, many hundred years, many thousand years had passed, King Makhādeva addressed his barber, "

msgctxt "mn83:4.2"
msgid "‘yadā me, samma kappaka, passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha me āroceyyāsī’ti. "
msgstr "‘My dear barber, when you see grey hairs growing on my head, please tell me.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn83:4.3"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako rañño maghadevassa paccassosi. "
msgstr "‘Yes, Your Majesty,’ replied the barber. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn83:4.4"
msgid "Addasā kho, ānanda, kappako bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena rañño maghadevassa sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni. "
msgstr "When many thousands of years had passed, the barber saw grey hairs growing on the king’s head. "

msgctxt "mn83:4.5"
msgid "Disvāna rājānaṃ maghadevaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He said to the king, "

msgctxt "mn83:4.6"
msgid "‘pātubhūtā kho devassa devadūtā, dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātānī’ti. "
msgstr "‘The messengers of the gods have shown themselves to you. Grey hairs can be seen growing on your head.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn83:4.7"
msgid "‘Tena hi, samma kappaka, tāni palitāni sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā mama añjalismiṃ patiṭṭhāpehī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Well then, my dear barber, carefully pull them out with tweezers and place them in my cupped hands.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn83:4.8"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako rañño maghadevassa paṭissutvā tāni palitāni sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā rañño maghadevassa añjalismiṃ patiṭṭhāpesi. "
msgstr "‘Yes, Your Majesty,’ replied the barber, and he did as the king said. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.76, sc3
msgctxt "mn83:4.9"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, rājā maghadevo kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ āmantāpetvā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The king gave the barber a prize village, then summoned the crown prince and said, "

msgctxt "mn83:4.10"
msgid "‘pātubhūtā kho me, tāta kumāra, devadūtā; "
msgstr "‘Dear prince, the messengers of the gods have shown themselves to me. "

msgctxt "mn83:4.11"
msgid "dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni; "
msgstr "Grey hairs can be seen growing on my head. "

msgctxt "mn83:4.12"
msgid "bhuttā kho pana me mānusakā kāmā; "
msgstr "I have enjoyed human pleasures. "

msgctxt "mn83:4.13"
msgid "samayo dibbe kāme pariyesituṃ. "
msgstr "Now it is time to seek heavenly pleasures. "

# NOTE: BB has “take over the kingship” But cp DN 26, “imaṃ samuddapariyantaṃ pathaviṃ paṭipajja”, which shows rajjam must be the place here, i.e. realm.
msgctxt "mn83:4.14"
msgid "Ehi tvaṃ, tāta kumāra, imaṃ rajjaṃ paṭipajja. "
msgstr "Come, dear prince, rule the realm. "

msgctxt "mn83:4.15"
msgid "Ahaṃ pana kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmi. "
msgstr "I shall shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn83:4.16"
msgid "Tena hi, tāta kumāra, yadā tvampi passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyāsi. "
msgstr "For dear prince, you too will one day see grey hairs growing on your head. When this happens, after giving a prize village to the barber and carefully instructing the crown prince in kingship, you should shave off your hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

msgctxt "mn83:4.17"
msgid "Yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ antimapuriso ahosi. "
msgstr "Keep up this good practice that I have founded. Do not be my final man. "

# NOTE: I am not comfortable with the syntax of this sentence, which appears to lack the expected pronouns. I wonder whether it could mean: “In whatever age of man is current that this good practice is broken, he is their last man.” But purisayuga elsewhere always means “pair of men”.
msgctxt "mn83:4.18"
msgid "Yasmiṃ kho, tāta kumāra, purisayuge vattamāne evarūpassa kalyāṇassa vattassa samucchedo hoti so tesaṃ antimapuriso hoti. "
msgstr "Whatever generation is current when such good practice is broken, he is their final man. "

msgctxt "mn83:4.19"
msgid "Taṃ tāhaṃ, tāta kumāra, evaṃ vadāmi—"
msgstr "Therefore I say to you, "

msgctxt "mn83:4.20"
msgid "yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ antimapuriso ahosī’ti. "
msgstr "“Keep up this good practice that I have founded. Do not be my final man.”’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, sc4
msgctxt "mn83:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, rājā maghadevo kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji. "
msgstr "And so, after giving a prize village to the barber and carefully instructing the crown prince in kingship, King Makhādeva shaved off his hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness here in this mango grove. "

#. VAR: abyābajjhena → abyāpajjhena (bj, s1-3, km) | avyāpajjhena (pts1) | abyāpajjena (mr)
msgctxt "mn83:5.2"
msgid "So mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi. "
msgstr "He meditated spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, he spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

msgctxt "mn83:5.3"
msgid "Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … "
msgstr "He meditated spreading a heart full of compassion … "

msgctxt "mn83:5.4"
msgid "muditāsahagatena cetasā … "
msgstr "rejoicing … "

msgctxt "mn83:5.5"
msgid "upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi. "
msgstr "equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, he spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc5
msgctxt "mn83:6.1"
msgid "Rājā kho panānanda, maghadevo caturāsītivassasahassāni kumārakīḷitaṃ kīḷi, caturāsītivassasahassāni oparajjaṃ kāresi, caturāsītivassasahassāni rajjaṃ kāresi, caturāsītivassasahassāni imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito brahmacariyamacari. "
msgstr "For 84,000 years King Makhādeva played games as a child, for 84,000 years he acted as viceroy, for 84,000 years he ruled the realm, and for 84,000 years he led the spiritual life after going forth here in this mango grove. "

msgctxt "mn83:6.2"
msgid "So cattāro brahmavihāre bhāvetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmalokūpago ahosi. "
msgstr "Having developed these four Brahmā meditations, when his body broke up, after death, he was reborn in a good place, a Brahmā realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
